==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zodiacal
<hw>Zo*di"a*cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>zodiacal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining
to the zodiac; situated within the zodiac; <as>as, the <ex>zodiacal</ex>
planets</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Zodiacal light</b></col>, <cd>a luminous tract of the
sky, of an elongated, triangular figure, lying near the ecliptic, its
base being on the horizon, and its apex at varying altitudes. It is to
be seen only in the evening, after twilight, and in the morning before
dawn. It is supposed to be due to sunlight reflected from multitudes of
meteoroids revolving about the sun nearly in the plane of the
ecliptic.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zoea</ent>⟦br⟧
